Installation: In your home directory check out the repository using the following command

    git clone git://github.com/samwhitlock/dotvim.git .vim

Then create the symlink for the vimrc file:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Now you need to update the submodules to grab all the plugins

    git submodule update --init

To update all the plugins, execute the following command to grab the latest 
version of all the plugins

    git submodule foreach git pull --ff-only origin master

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Disclaimer: I don't claim to be a vim expert at all. The stuff in here is likely 
to be terribly misconfigured, but I'm only a novice. Use at your own risk!
